<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94115 Exchange/7–145:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20T20:00:00-04:00">July
                                        20, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2357. Urtel 3377 July 1. Gorgé should be requested report grounds for
                                suggesting exchange through Siberia at this time. Dept had
                                understood from earlier reports facilities not available overland or
                                sea transportation any appreciable number exchangees to Siberia. If
                                Gorgé now believes any real progress could be made Dept would like
                                his views for use in shaping proposals.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>